Trim the @pak choi{1}, slice the green leaf from the stalk and set aside for later, then
thinly slice the remainder widthways. Trim the @radishes{100} and thinly slice. Trim the
@carrot{1}. Use a #vegetable peeler{} to peel long ribbons from all sides of the length
of the carrot. Stop when you get to the centre, discard the centre. Pop the chopped
bok choy, radishes and carrot in a #bowl{} and set aside for later. Peel and grate the
@garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Halve the
@burger buns{2}.

Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Chop the @sweet potato{2} into 2cm wide wedges (no need
to peel!). Pop the wedges on a large #baking tray{} in a single layer. Drizzle with
@oil{drizzle}, then season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Toss to coat, then spread out
and set aside. Trim the @aubergine{1} and slice into rounds 2cm wide. Pop on another
baking tray in a single layer and drizzle with @oil{drizzle}.

Roast the potatoes on the top shelf and the aubergines on the middle until the
potatoes are nearly tender and the aubergine is soft and golden, ~{15-20%minutes}.
Once the time is up, remove the aubergine from the oven and set aside, drizzle two
thirds of the @honey{45} over the sweet potato and pop back into the oven until golden
and tender, ~{10-15%minutes} more.

Pop the @panko breadcrumbs{25%g} in a bowl and add the garlic, half the
@ginger puree{1} and half the @miso paste{30%g}. Mix together, then add the
@British beef mince{360%g}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and mix together with
your hands until well combined. Shape into burgers about 2cm thick, 2 per person.
> Remember to wash your hands after handling raw meat!

Heat a #frying pan{} on medium high heat (no oil). Once hot, add the
@sesame seeds{15%g} and toast them until golden, ~{2-3%minutes}, stirring them
regularly so they don't burn. Remove the seeds to a bowl, keeping the pan.

Pop your pan back on medium high heat, add a drizzle of @oil{drizzle}. Once hot, add
the burgers, fry until browned on the outside and cooked through, ~{8-10%minutes}
total. Carefully turn them every ~{3%minutes}, lower the heat if they are burning.
> The burgers are cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Remove to a #plate{} and cover with #foil{}. Meanwhile, add the @mayonnaise{2} and
@water{1} to the sesame seeds along with the remaining ginger puree. Stir together.
Put the remaining miso, remaining honey and @soy sauce{25} into another bowl and
stir together.

Pop your pan back on medium high heat and add the cooked aubergine. Pour in the
miso mixture and turn the aubergine so it's coated in the sauce. Simmer until the
sauce is sticky, ~{3-4%minutes}. Pop the burger buns in the oven to warm through,
~{2-3%minutes}. Meanwhile, add half the mayo dressing to the radish, bok choy and
carrot, toss to coat. Serve one burger on the bottom of the bun, followed by a couple
of slices of aubergine, another burger and some more aubergine. Finish with the
bok choy leaf, a dollop of remaining dressing and the bun lid. Serve with the wedges
and salad. Enjoy!